text: Zeale nigromaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Johann Christoph Friedrich Klug in 1829. It is known from Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, and Uruguay."Zeale nigromaculata". BioLib. Retrieved 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Lamiinae Category:Beetles described in 1829
